# Project Structure and Naming Conventions

This document describes the directory structure of the project and its naming conventions.

## Monorepo layout

```
src/
    eduriam-ui-core/                # Package: @eduriam-ui/core
    eduriam-ui-<theme-variant>/     # Package: @eduriam-ui/<theme-variant> - (e.g. @eduriam-ui/minimal)
```

## Naming conventions

- Directories use **kebab-case**, except component folders which use **PascalCase**.
  - Examples:
    - `theme/`, `utils/`, `hooks/` (kebab-case)
    - `ExampleButton/`, `ExampleCheckbox/` (PascalCase component folders)
- TypeScript sources in `src/` with explicit extensions (`.ts`, `.tsx`).
- Each package exposes a single public entry via `src/index.ts`.

## Package layout (applies to each package under `src/*`)

```
src/<package-name>/
  package.json
  tsconfig.json
  src/
    index.ts                   # Package public surface
    theme/                     # Shared theme tokens
      index.ts
      palette.ts
      typography.ts
    components/                # Components grouped by folder (PascalCase)
      ExampleButton/
        ExampleButton.tsx
        ExampleButton.stories.tsx
        index.ts
      ExampleCheckbox/
        ExampleCheckbox.tsx
        ExampleCheckbox.stories.tsx
        index.ts
```

## Components

- One component per folder using PascalCase naming convention
- Inside each component folder:
  - `<Name>.tsx`: component implementation
  - `index.ts`: re-exports for convenient imports
  - `<Name>.stories.tsx`: co-located Storybook story with interaction tests

## Theme tokens

- Keep shared tokens in `theme/` (kebab-case directory).
- Example public exports: `palette`, `typography` from `@eduriam-ui/core`, and overrides in `@eduriam-ui/minimal`.

## Storybook

- Story placement is co-located with components in each package `components/<Name>/<Name>.stories.tsx`. Interaction tests are located in the same file.
